beer_description: European Pilsner malt offers sweetness balanced by a spicy hop profile. "Pau Hana" is a Hawaiian phrase meaning 'finished work'. This beer is perfect for when your day is over, ... and over...

Our IPA is less ordinary from somewhere extraordinary. Generously hopped to 60 IBUs with Yakima Valley hops our IPA is thirst quenching, with a pronounced citrus flavor and a full malty body. Brewed with Centennial hops and two-row Pale & Crystal malt. Our Northwest-style IPA has won 14 gold medals and was named The Americas Best at the 2014 World Beer Awards. ABV 6% IBU 60
Sour beer with fresh Belgian cherries (Kelleries) (25 kg/hl)

Our Autumn Scrumpy has wine like characters and is bright in colour.
It is well balanced on the palate and releases a wonderful apple aroma.
Autumn Scrumpy is made from specially selected apples that have been sourced from our local growers to make a premium quality Scrumpy.
Our trailblazing Double IPA hauls a bold hop profile featuring heavy pine, orange rind, and guava with a sweet malty finish.

beer_description: This Abbey Style Dubbel Ale earns its appellation by being brewed with double the normal grain bill and the addition of Belgian dark candy sugar.  Fermenting with Trappist yeast creates dark fruit esters. Pilser, Pale, Extra Special and Chocolate malts evoke classic Belgian Ale sweet aromas with a hint of nuttiness. Use of Hallertau Hersbrucker and German Select hops enhance authenticity and provide a restrained bittering of 20 IBUs and a slight spicy aroma.
Our Imperial Porter is dark like a moonless night with blood red hues.  It has a rich and full favor of bittersweet chocolate and toasted malts with a hoppy dry finish.

A crisp, refreshing, light-bodied malt-flavored beer with a well-balanced finish. A Lager that drinks like a Pilsner. A liquid embodiment of living life to the fullest. A beverage made from pure spring water and the choicest hops. A beer with such good taste, it?s chosen you to drink it.
brewery.brewery_name: Cervecer?a Cuauht?moc Moctezuma S.A. de C.V.

beer_description:
It's fall, the leaves are beginning to turn, there is a bite in the air, and you hear the faint sound of Canadian Geese honking in the distance.  This means two things.  First, it's time to dig out that old camouflage jacket and spruce up the duck blind and secondly, it's time to head to your local watering hold and order a pint of Duck, Duck, Goose.  
    This American Porter showcases the beauty of properly combined chocolate, crystal, and munich malts.  Creating a smooth, chocolate forward porter that is easy to drink and packs enough punch to keep you warm all winter long.  How else are you going to console yourself after all those missed shots?
Brewed according to the German Purity Law of 1516. By masterbrewer Wolfgang Lindell
Brewed with fresh oyster. A smooth drinking aromatic stout with a discernible but unidentifiable aromatic aspect. Not suitable for vegetarians.

Deep amber with a light, creamy head; the nose starts off with a touch of citrus, but then turns decidedly into peaches. Tastes of creamy malt resulting from the pale 2 row and caramel malts and Saint Arnold yeast. Hop bitter starts low then builds to a crescendo, but always maintains a balance even in its big finish and continues to be peaches ? an interesting manifestation of the Columbus, Simcoe and Centennial hops. This is the first Divine Reserve to be filtered. This decision was made to make the hop flavors brighter. Best enjoyed at 45? or even a little warmer.

It?s no secret that it gets pretty cold here in Colorado. So early on in the brewery?s history, our brewmasters wanted to create a beer that would do the trick on a snowy winter day. Today, we craft our winter wonder with roasted malts and dark. Belgian candi sugar for rich caramel and toffee notes. It?s perfect on those winter days when you?re stuck inside.

brewery.brewery_name: Hair of the Dog Brewing Company

beer_description: A tribute to a local icon, this dark, smooth and easy drinking ale has hints of raisins and dark chocolate on the nose with plenty of roasted coffee and cocoa lingering on the finish.

Hofbr?uhaus is a symbol of Munich?s hospitality and the Bavarian gift for creating a snug and cosy atmosphere. Beer-lovers from all over the world come here to enjoy its famous beers. More than any other, Hofbr?u Original embodies the special atmosphere of the beer-making capital of Munich, and exports it to the four corners of the globe. Its refreshing, bitter flavour and alcoholic content of around 5.1% volume have made it famous worldwide. A Munich beer with character.

The Hangman is a big, brash American-style Pale Ale that features a huge hit of citrus and stone fruit hop notes on the nose. Brewed with American Ale yeast and a solid malt backbone ? Crystal and Carapils to be exact ? The Hangman showcases Cascade and Liberty hops, with plenty thrown late in the kettle for extra flavour.
5.3% ABV for export

Nutcracker Ale is Boulevard?s holiday gift for real beer lovers. This hearty, warming brew is a classic winter ale, deep amber in color, with hints of molasses balanced by the ?spiciness? of Chinook hops.

Originally a bottled special to celebrate the Great Western Railway 175th Anniversary.

A full flavoured bitter, chestnut brown in colour with a fruity aroma and smooth rich taste.
The robust flavor comes from the dark roasted malts and is accented with an espresso-roast coffee from our friends and neighbors at Charleston Coffee Roasters.

Our flagship IPA drinks like an ode to hoppy goodness. Galena, Cascade, and Nelson Sauvin hops burst forth with intense flavors of melon, grapefruit , and pineapple, while the body balances malt character with a pronounced dry finish.

beer_description: A classic beer for those beer lovers who love their hops, Happy Camper IPA will take the Pepsi Challenge (or IPA challenge, as we say in New Mexico) against any other pretenders to the throne. Was it divine providence that made this beer the king of the IPA world? Was it a tireless pursuit of glory? No, this IPA has a top-secret recipe to thank for its success, and this meticulously formulated combination of several different hops combined with a very specific brewing process give Happy Camper IPA a spicy, citric, and floral infusion of hop character, which is masterfully counterbalanced with the full-bodied maltiness characteristic of the Santa Fe Brewing Company?s distinctive beers.

The Butcher is a traditional-style Robust Porter with a twist. Brewed with Ale and Crystal malts, the beer sidesteps around tradition with the addition of chocolate malt, to darken and add flavour, as well as flaked oats to create a silky smooth finish. The combined malt profile creates a beer that is richly complex in flavour, while being incredibly balanced and drinkable, that pays homage to the great beer style that is Porter.
65 IBU

An easy drinking and refreshing IPA. Fresh dry hop, herbal character is provided by the mix of Challenger and First Gold hops. The use of crystal malt in the grist gives a satisfying toffee/caramel note and the addition of a little black malt adds just enough astringency to give a clean, dry finish.

Malts: Pale, crystal and black malt.

Hops: Challenger, Pilgrim and First Gold.

An award-winning American barleywine boasting a dense, 
fruity bouquet, an intense flavor palate and a deep reddish-brown color. Its big maltiness is superbly balanced by a wonderfully bittersweet hoppiness.

??Bigfoot captures the imagination, and its character is as big as the name implies, with a huge hoppiness in its earthy aroma, a chewy palate, and a great depth of flavor.?

Michael Jackson, Michael Jackson?s Beer
Using a fresh, custom blend of coffee beans roasted locally in Kalamazoo by Water Street Coffee Joint, this dark, roasty stout matches an intense flavor with an unmistakable aromatic punch.
A balance of malt flavor and sweetness

Sunset in color, brewed with a combination of pale and crystal malts, London yeast, and a variety of traditional English hops for a spicy, slightly bittersweet finish and a wonderful fruity and flowery aroma.

Copper colored with a clean finish, this Extra Special Bitter (ESB) has it all; a fruity, malty flavor and a subtle lingering bitterness. If you like dry, hoppy beers this one is for you. Mahogany Ale - one taste and you?re hooked.

Brewed with Australian ale malt, along with Munich and Crystal malts, The Governor is the perfect Friday night knock-off beer. The use of all new Australian hop varieties Topaz and Galaxy ? along with the latest American hop variety, Mosaic ? gives The Governor aromas of citrus and stone fruit on the nose. Actually, with its refreshing, light bitterness, this Golden Ale is the perfect anytime beer.

beer_description:
0.0% alcohol, without depriving yourself!
This beer has everything that makes an original WARSTEINER outstanding. In short: 100% premium enjoyment. Naturally brewed according to the German Reinheitsgebot (Purity Law) from 1516, all of the alcohol is drawn from this top pilsener, but only after the beer has fully matured.

An exceptionally smooth, dark, German Pilsener
Thanks to only the best ingredients this dark refreshes like a true lager beer. It has a rich smooth taste and a lingering slightly sweet aftertaste. The delicate aroma and extraordinary coloration result from a careful barley malt roasting process.

Above and beyond an India Pale Ale--I2PA is radically hopped with an intense aroma and hop bitterness. Unfiltered and aged for 9 months before it leaves the brewery--not for the faint of heart. I2PA is brewed with two-row Pipkin Pale malts, Saaz, Cascade and Northwest Golding hops. I2PA is available in a new 750ml Silkscreened black ceramic bottle and on draft.

St. Bridget, a legendary Irish saint, created a sensation by turning her bathwater into beer. What better way to celebrate her worthy miracle than with our zymurgistic tribute to her feat: St. Bridget's Porter. St. Bridget's is a smooth and elegant brown porter. Brimming with coffee and chocolate characteristics from dark barley malts, St. Bridget's is carefully hopped to provide the perfect complement to its malty robustness. This beer is a "must have" beer for all porter lovers.

Prepare yourself for a religious experience

beer_description: A Classic Amber Ale , balancing six select malts with English Fuggle hops and naturally carbonated for a rich creamy finish.
a full bodied copper color Pale Ale prepared with Americsn Hops and caramelized malts.

Chili in the aroma. Chili on the palate. Chili. Pairs well with a ... chili.
Premium lager beer with a chili pepper added.
beer_name: Original C Cave Creek Chili Beer - Cerveza Con Chili

beer_description: Brewed with pale malt that?s been smoked with native mesquite in the backyard of the brewery in Shiner, Texas, this refreshing German style Rauchbier  has a smoky flavor that goes great with all the flavors of summer.
Scurvy India Pale Ale (IPA) India Pale Ale Brewed With Orange Peel. An ample ale, exploding with luscious, fruity hops and citrusy blast of orange zest. Ready to walk the plank, Matey

In San Diego, we?re not known for our partridges or pears but we can all relate to those noisy parrots and their relentless ?caroling?. Parrot in a Palm Tree is a robust Baltic Porter brewed especially for the Holidays. Aged three months in San Pasqual Tawny Port barrels, the resulting brew isn?t for the birds. This winter warmer boasts a complex bouquet of dark fruits, espresso and chocolate, with hints of oak in its warming finish. Raise a glass to 2010 or save a bottle as this limited release will age with the best of them.
beer_name: Parrot In A Palm Tree Holiday Baltic Porter

beer_description: This is our Russian Imperial stout aged for at least six months in whiskey or bourbon barrels (we switch it up from time to time). This is a must try for any true stout  or barrel aged beer lover.

Cascade Blackberry Ale spends over 6 months of lactic fermentaion and aging in small oak barrels. This "Belgian Flanders Style Red Ale" is refermented with fresh whole Northwest Blackberries and then hand bottled. Cascade Blackberry Ale is bottle fermented and should be refrigerated or stored at cellar temp and served at 45-50 degrees.

Lagrimas Negras, style oatmeal stout, our beer is flavored with the elixir of Moctezuma: xocoati, considered by the pre-Columbian culture as the food of the gods. Contains a blend of malts, toasted oats and about cacao, we smooth delivery and refined flavors and aromas in every sip. From smooth to the palate foam body has a creamy texture with one of the world's best flavors: chocolate.

Buc?falo, named after the black horse of Alexander the Great, legend of strength unmountable is our stout imperial style beer, combined with the glorious taste of Mexican coffee, has an almost black color, mix of malts and roasted coffee beans. Beer that balances the taste and texture, with a thin layer of dense, dark brown foam that can amaze anyone.
Non-alcoholic malt drink.
2009 winner created by Ben Miller.
beer_name: Samuel Adams Longshot Mile High Barleywine

beer_description: One of Warren's favorite pastimes back in the 30's was a trip to the city dump to shoot rats?so much that it was a common date for him and his wife-to-be, Casey. The manager of the city dump was John Schmaltz?hence the nickname "Schmaltz" Marti. We hope you enjoy our Schmaltz's Alt, a creamy smooth dark alt brewed even better than before.

De Dulle Teve is brewed in the tradition of a Belgian Triple. Its high density stems from large amounts of pale malt increased with pale candi sugar in the brew kettle. Unfiltered, unpasteurized, bottle-conditioned. 

De Dulle Teve keeps two to three years without major changes in taste. Further maturing, up to 10 years, will cause it to darken a little and lose some of its bitterness. The bittering of about 30 IBU is due to Goldings hops in the brew kettle.

Our other famous Belgian-style offering is our Grand Cru. As with Horny Devil, it is fermented using yeast which originated in a Trappist monastery in Belgium. A darker type of Belgian candi sugar gives it more color and a richer complexity of flavor, consistent with the Belgian style. Qualities Medium-dark brown, with tan head. Sweet, malty aroma with a satisfying balance of hoppiness. Tremendously intriguing, complex flavors play upon the palate shifting from sweet to tangy to hoppy and so on. The medium-dryfinish leaves you eager for the next sip. Awards Multiple awards, including Silver and Bronze in its category at the California State Fair, multiple years.

You can?t hold your head up in fine brewing circles these days without a decent India Pale Ale in your repertoire, and Tuatara makes this one true to form. Traditionally, IPAs were brewed with prodigious hopping so they?d make the trip to the Raj in one piece, but the brewing itself was actually done in the mother country. Tuatara?s is a proper English-style IPA. That means a full malt body, not too dark in colour, and hopped up for plenty of bitterness with proper corblimey-how?s-your-father English hops. There?s nothing better.
(special blend)

The Red Racer winter ale is a classic recipe with a smooth balance of winter spice and Northwest-style hop flavour. The hops add a bitterness to the back of the palate while the winter spices are reminiscent of your favourite holiday treat.
Very Smooth Lager

Huda is a traditional Vietnamese beer brewed and bottled in Hu?, Vietnam, by Hue Breweries Ltd. Being aromatic and refreshing with a slightly "hoppy" bouquet, Huda is a favorite beer among many domestic and foreign consumers.

The Huda beer has been a symbol of the Heartland for more than 25 years and its reputation for quality is a source of pride among local Huda consumers. The good quality of the beer also caused Huda to win a silver medal at the World Beer Championships in 2013.
Famous Ukrainian lager, brewed with old world recipes, using the finest ingredients.

Het blonde Tripel Ram?ebier (7,5%) wordt gebrouwen naar een eeuwenoud Haspengouws recept. Een tweede gisting vindt plaats in de fles, waardoor de smaak nog intenser wordt.
Om volop te kunnen genieten van de aroma's, raden we u aan dit bier te degusteren bij een temperatuur die schommelt tussen 7? en 10?. Let wel op het bodempje gist dat zich onderaan in de fles bevindt, sommige bierkenners vinden dit net lekker, andere verkiezen dit niet mee op te drinken.

The triple blond is both simple and complex. Its initial simplicity, with an easy approach that releases a sweet zest is quickly complemented by a bitterness that runs to the back of the mouth. Complex, with its raw ingredients clashing a little like cannon shots, but each tastier than the last, with alternating bitter hops and the flexibility of its malt, gives this Waterloo beer the taste of victory.

A coffee nose is combined with a tone of roots, but with a strong, disciplined character. Its flavour develops gradually, reminiscent, if you will, of the ardor of the soldiers of the Battle of Waterloo. Strong and reassuring, it provides a conclusion that tends primarily towards the sweet at the finish, a symbol of a well-deserved treat at the end of a busy day.

Unlike a typical Red Ale, Believer balances a rich malt complexity with a plentiful hop presence. Notes of caramel, toffy, fig, and date ease into earthy and floral hops, making this Double Red Ale incredibly drinkable and full-flavored.

The full complexity of the genuine Bavarian wheat beer ?great with hearty food.

Amber-mahogany colored wheat beer. Nuances of ripe bananas, clove, nutmeg and nuts create the aroma. A full-bodied and sparkling beer with a harmonious finish.
Brewed according to the original recipe of the founder of the brewery of 1872. 
The ideal companion for Bavarian food, hearty dishes, roast poark, ?Leberk?se? (meat loaf), the Bavarian ?Wei?wurst? (white sausage), marinated shrimps, camembert or olives stuffed with peppers.
